page.title: 20Children's Rhymes
page.content: Choosing Rhymes - Black shoe, black shoe, Change your black shoe. - Racing car number 9 losing gallons all the time. How many gallons did it lose - l,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9,10. - Boy scout, walk out, turn a dirty dishcloth inside out. OUT spells out and you must jolly well go. - Bluebell, cockleshells, evey, ivy over. Polly in the kitchen. Doing a bit of stitching. How many stitches did she do altogether. - Down Mississippi if you miss a link you're out, you're in. - Vote, vote for little (name) in comes (name) at the door (name) is the one having all the fun, so we don't want (name) any more. Kick her out, shut the door, say no more.
